Deutsche Bahn is currently testing the hassle-free ticket control.
You simply confirm by phone that you have taken your place and thus devalue the ticket.
A test operation is currently running on two routes.
"If the offer comes up, let's expand it.
It is expected to be available on many other long-distance routes in Germany at the beginning of next year," said a rail spokesman.
"Comfort check-in" the train calls the ticket devaluation without Schaffner.
